<br>
Usually as a Druid at this lvl I snare pets, and do not even bother with snaring the pets owner.  Against Mages and Necros this then became a casting fight each of us trying to outnuke/DOT/Heal each other.  Even with there pet slowly chasing us Mages and Necros can take care of themselves.<br>
<br>
As a Beastlord when my pet gets snared its much harder to do damage to the druid/necro as we can not do a significant amount of spell damage as a mage/necro would.  If they can get me snared its over but most of the time it ends with me fleeing and then trying to bandage/heal thru DOTS.<br>
<br>
I am usually fighting people in the 60-50 range and snare, FOL, and root just dont stick.  I love PKing with both chars I just havent found a good strategy against classes that can snare my pet and blast away and of course Bards and them using the pet poof trick (This needs to fixed along with Bard AE fear) <p>Ladon Thornpaw Lvl 58 Preserver <BR>
