She then started bow kiting me. It was kind of sad really, id be rooted for a full minute and take less than 100 points of damage the whole time. She for some reason wasnt shooting at me from a large distance so often when root would break id get in a round or two of combat before I was rerooted which evened out the damage. It was very close and I was at 20% life when she finally died (thank you mend) but the point of this is that snare doesnt HAVE to mean certain death. I have dueled on both sides of the game as a monk and as a druid,(druids can kick ass in a duel btw lol) and while snares and rots do give an advantage you just have to keep your focus in a duel and remember not to panic. <br>
An example of how to even things up a bit in a duel against a snarer. If you are Vah shir you get safe fall, try to fight near cliffs and such and when the person is focused on chasing you down to get the los needed to nuke you try to head for the largest drop off you can reach and watch them tumble after you. I have seen them kill themselves in ew by falling off the edges of the zone lol. <br>
Another way that might work in pk land is this. You can cast invis on your pets right? Well a bl shares the ability to wear armor like a monks that doesnt always show up on your char so what you do is have your fully buffed pet invisible and you wander around barehanded and looking naked as if you were on a cr or something. Then when the pker attacks thinking he has an easy kill WHAMMO! You send in your pet and put on your weapons and he wont know what hit him! <br>
One last tip that I developed with my druid that will work even better with beast lords considering the many idiots who play is this. Most people dont expect a pet reliant class to be able to melee well! I have defeated mages in duels simply by rooting the pet fast and running up to MELEE the mage! I would nuke in between attacks but my whailing away not only allowed me to do more damage it also gave me an occaisional interrupt! As has been mentioned before people still seem to be surprised at the damage we can do in melee combat so they often expect you to play the caster role of hanging back and casting and letting the pet do the melee damage but they get a rude awakening and a quick lesson in bl versatility when they see our fists heading for their soft caster bodies! <br>
Dont lose heart guys! We are still a new class so people arent sure of our capabilities so that gives us an edge when fighting them. We may not be the top class in pvp lol but we also arent yet the worst!<br>
