beastlords do pretty well with just dispell and send pet and yourself in with sow but over 40 we are talking about real nukes, dots and dmg dealer so you really dont get alot of time to fight or time to flee for that matter.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Things to keep in mind:  <br>
<br>
Most pkers mr is above 100, for example my 52 sk had 140mr and up at all times when traveling or pking.<br>
<br>
monks, sks, necros can fd and our pets will return to us so we have to send them back to fight<br>
<br>
My beastlord is lvl 52 at moment, and not plved but has decent gear.<br>
<br>
Pumice...near all pkers i know have pumice and use it..unless those few classes that get a decent dispel magic<br>
<br>
With near all classes with levitate, they will outrun your pet, and you can not mele if they levitated<br>
<br>
Pets are nerfed in dmg they deal in pvp<br>
<br>
Rouge:  55plus<br>
<br>
Fought few rougues, one  i keep having conflicts with.  My group killed him once so think he has a vindeta.  He can double backstab for over 300 per hit equalling 600dmg if he catches ya good.  I nearly did well agaist him..kited him around for long time, got dispelled resowed kited some more eventually died because i was in an area where i could not kite far because of mob agroes.   Yes i did try casting on him few times with all resists, but for one cast loosing 300 or more hp is not worth it.  <br>
<br>
Monk: lvl 53<br>
<br>
Fought many many monks..i swore this one was going to be cake.  Saw another beastlord in zone, was going to fight him..when monk jumped me.  Fight was going well, kited him around some, tried casting some spells..ehh all resists again..but back to pumice..so ensure he at jboot speed or less.  Well to my suprise he turned on pet, because with other pet classes this is big no no.  I healed my pet up once but after all the previous casting on this guy with resists i was oom.  Tried to mele him while he killed pet with very little dmg being done and i jetted outa there. *sigh*<br>
<br>
<br>
Pally:  low 50s one and 59lvl one<br>
<br>
Pally of equal level is semi close match, except with the new lucin 2handers coming out, its unlikely you want to go head to head with somone who can double hit for 200each time equaling 400hp dmg to you.  But there are ways to be outa his range and mele him or staffe to side and get in some shots, but it takes alot of our shots to equal one good swing of his.  The higher lvl pally just rooted me and meled me to death.<br>
<br>
Druid:  fought many many of the favorite newb chars).<br>
<br>
In the low 50s range, i generally resist snare root ect but pet even with mr buff neally always gets snare on him.  Once in So ro desert i encounterd think he was 54 druid.  Off the bat i pumiced him in attempt to drop lev, sow and hp buff.  Dropped lots, but not sow.  He snared my pet which was on him.  Pet hits for average 24pts of dmg against druids ive fought which is slightly less than his high of 53pts.  Anyways, im pissed so i kite him around for bit waiting for snare to drop off pet, and loose him so i could dispell winged death and another dot he put on me.  Bah, two charges of pumice gone but still have some dot still on me and pet is mia.  I load of cancel magic, 5 casts later the other dot is gone...i summon pet, and it takes 4 casts to drop the snare of him. <br>
<br>
<br>
